Brett Goldstein and Imogen Poots challenge the notion of a soulmate in All of You. 

All of You premieres September 26 on Apple TV+ https://apple.co/_AllofYou

Best friends since college, Simon (Emmy Award winner Brett Goldstein) and Laura (Imogen Poots) drift apart when she takes a test that finds her soulmate despite years of unspoken feelings between them. Over the years, as their paths cross and diverge, neither can deny the feeling that they’ve missed out on a life together. Faced with the uncertainty of changing the course of their lives, are Simon and Laura willing to risk everything to experience the love that had been between them all along, or should they accept their fate? 

“All of You” explores whether one person can ever be your everything in this humorous and heart-wrenching romantic drama co-written by Goldstein and Emmy Award winner William Bridges (“Black Mirror”), who also directs. Hailing from MRC, the film is produced by Ryder Picture Company’s Aaron Ryder and Andrew Swett, and Bridges and Goldstein also produce.

snippet.title: Nuremberg | Official Teaser 2 | Starring Russell Crowe, Rami Malek & Michael Shannon
snippet.description:
Watch teaser two of James Vanderbilt's Nuremberg, with a first glimpse of Richard E. Grant as Sir David Maxwell-Fyfe.

Nuremberg, inspired by Jack El-Hai’s The Nazi and the Psychiatrist, brings to life the true story of the Nuremberg Trials that followed World War Two.

The film follows American psychiatrist Douglas Kelley (Rami Malek), assigned to assess the mental fitness of high-ranking Nazi prisoners. His most challenging subject is Hermann Göring (Russell Crowe), Hitler’s closest confidant, leading to a tense psychological battle.

Written and directed by James Vanderbilt, the film unfolds as a gripping cat-and-mouse drama. Nuremberg features a stellar ensemble cast, including Michael Shannon, Richard E. Grant, and Leo Woodall as translator Howard Triest. Set in the shadow of the unimaginable crimes committed during the war, Nuremberg explores the human mind at its most chilling and complex.

Nuremberg, a Sky Original film, will be available in UK cinemas on November 14, 2025.

snippet.title: Marsh DJ Set - Live From Gjipe, Albania
snippet.description:
Marsh DJ Set - Live from Gjipe, Albania: 

‘They say preparation is everything, unless you bring a mouse to a DJ booth….
Months of planning, hours of edits… and five minutes before my Gjipe set, I realised my USB was still at the hotel 🙃

A crazy day. I spend so long preparing these mixes, digging through Beatport, promos, demos, and other people’s mixes to find hidden gems. By the time I record, I’ve edited many of the tracks and tested every transition multiple times. For Gjipe, I had a full three-hour set ready, still tweaking that very morning to make it perfect.

When I arrived, the weather was incredible and my spirits were high. Five minutes before, I went to plug in my USB… only to realise, with horror, that it wasn’t in my bag. In the morning rush, I’d packed my Magic Mouse instead. Same shape, similar case, but not much use behind the decks! I’ve never done this before, and of course the one time it happened, I was a boat ride away from my hotel!

Some of you probably saw the blood drain from my face. I told Mia to keep playing (she was smashing it to be fair!) while I sprinted back to the boat. The round trip took about 45 minutes, but I made it back with my USB ready to go.

Then came plot twist number two: I finished my set at 6pm and was told I still had 30 minutes left. I’d gotten my set time wrong all along! Between rushing from breakfast, the boat rides, and the USB chaos, I never realised I wasn’t due to start until 3:30 (not 3:00) and finish at 6:30.

In the end, maybe the chaos was a blessing. It forced me to think on my feet, play to the crowd, and select the strongest tracks from my setlist. It wasn’t the day I planned, but it became a set I’ll never forget and I hope it’s a blessing to you too!’ 

- Marsh
